Package org.openlca.core.database.references

Class Reference

java.lang.Object
org.openlca.core.database.references.Reference
All Implemented Interfaces:
Serializable
public class Reference extends Object implements Serializable
Describes an entity $e_r$ which is referenced from an entity $e_o$ where $e_o$ is the owner of the reference and $e_r$ is the referenced entity. For example, if a process has a reference to a location then the process takes the role of $e_o$ and the location of $e_r$ in that reference.

  • Field Details

    • ownerId

      public final long ownerId
      The owner of the reference, e.g. if a process has a reference to a location, the process is the owner.

    • ownerType

      public final String ownerType
      The type of the owner of the references.

    • id

      The ID of the referenced entity $e_r$

    • type

      public final String type
      The type of the referenced entity $e_r$.

    • property

      public final String property
      This is typically the name of the field in which the reference is stored in the owner $e_o$.

    • nestedOwnerId

      public final long nestedOwnerId
      The can be intermediate objects in a reference between an owner $e_o$ and a referenced entity $e_r$. For example in a reference process -> exchange -> flow, the exchange would be such an intermediate object. This field holds the ID of such an intermediate object in this case.

    • nestedOwnerType

      public final String nestedOwnerType
      The type of the intermediate object, if present.

    • nestedProperty

      public final String nestedProperty
      The field in which the intermediate object is stored in the owner $e_o$ if present.

    • optional

      public final boolean optional
      Indicates whether a reference is optional or not. In general a reference is optional if it does not break the calculation when it is missing or broken. For example, the unit of an exchange is not optional but the data set generator of a process is.
